  "hash": "sha256:a3f7c2e10d94b856f2c3a1e7d08b4f5c9e2d6a1b3f8c7e4d2a9b0f1e6c5d3a2b",
  "signature": "ed25519:b1d4e7a2f9c3b6e0d5a8f2c1e4b7d0a3f6c9e2b5d8a1f4c7e0b3d6a9f2c5e8b1",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA must demonstrate version-controlled solver builds, automated regression testing across all hemolysis-relevant flow regimes, and documented change-management procedures consistent with IEC 62304 Class C practices. Gradation 4 requires traceable test coverage reports reviewed by an independent SQA authority.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM 9) is managed under git version control with tagged release builds. Automated regression tests cover 12 canonical benchmark cases. However, independent SQA review has not been formally completed and test coverage metrics for non-Newtonian blood rheology subroutines are absent. Achieved level is Gradation 3; required Gradation 4 is not met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification must include manufactured-solution tests for all active PDEs including the hemolysis transport equation, with observed order-of-accuracy within 10% of theoretical order. Gradation 4 requires published or independently audited verification suite results.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to Navier-Stokes and scalar transport equations. Observed spatial order of accuracy is 1.87 versus theoretical 2.0 (6.5% deviation). The hemolysis power-law transport equation MMS test is documented internally but has not been independently audited. Achieved Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at the design operating point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM). Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the hemolysis index QoI is 8.3%, which exceeds the MRL-5 target of ≤3%. Coarser meshes were necessary due to computational resource constraints on the rotating impeller passage. Achieved Gradation 3 against required Gradation 5. The required level reflects the absolute hemolysis threshold decision context at MRL 5, where discretization errors directly propagate into patient-risk conclusions; however, no structured acceptanceCriteria record was registered in the evidence package at the time of assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope (flow 3–8 L/min, rotational speed 2400–3600 RPM) with blood analog viscosity within ±5% of target and temperature controlled to 37±0.5°C. Gradation 4 requires in-vitro tests with ovine or porcine blood rather than analog fluid alone.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests used a glycerol-water blood analog at matched viscosity and density. Temperature was controlled to 37±0.3°C. Five operating points were tested. No animal blood tests were performed; analog fluid was used throughout. This limits equivalency for hemolysis yield calculations. Achieved Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Output comparison must address both velocity field and scalar hemolysis index QoIs using quantitative metrics (e.g., E_rms, U_num/U_exp ratio). Gradation 4 requires uncertainty-weighted comparison with experimental uncertainty fully characterised and propagated.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field comparison against PIV data shows E_rms of 14% averaged across the five operating points. Hemolysis index predictions deviate from experimental values by 18–42% depending on operating point. Experimental uncertainty for hemolysis measurements is only partially characterised (random error quantified; systematic bias from assay method not characterised). Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must directly map to the clinical decision metric (absolute hemolysis index, plasma-free haemoglobin threshold). Gradation 4 requires documented traceability from each computational QoI to a specific regulatory acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) computed from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks. NIH is directly compared against the clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100 L established in the device submission. Traceability from CFD output to regulatory threshold is fully documented. Achieved Gradation 4; requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on a geometry and flow regime that is representative of the VAD COU. Gradation 5 requires validation on the same device geometry at all COU operating points with blood (not analog). Gradation 3 permits analog-fluid validation on a surrogate geometry.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which is a standardised surrogate rather than the sponsor's specific VAD impeller geometry. Blood analog fluid was used. The operating envelope partially overlaps the COU (3 of 5 operating points within range). Spatial and geometric differences between the generic pump and the VAD impeller introduce extrapolation uncertainty. Achieved Gradation 3 against required Gradation 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver iterative convergence must be demonstrated with residuals below 1e-6 for all equations and solution-change norms below 0.01% over the final 500 iterations. Gradation 4 requires automated convergence monitoring with halting criteria enforced by the solver control script.",
      "rationale": "Iterative residuals for continuity and momentum reach 1e-4 at steady-state; the hemolysis scalar transport equation stalls at 5e-4 for two of five operating points. Automated convergence monitoring is implemented but the halting threshold was manually overridden to allow submission of results within the project timeline. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Use error assessment must include documented simulation setup checklists, independent review of boundary condition assignments, and at least one blind re-run by a second analyst. Gradation 3 requires evidence that all checklist items were reviewed by an independent engineer.",
      "rationale": "A simulation setup checklist covering 34 items was completed by the lead analyst. Boundary conditions were reviewed by a second team member for three of five operating points. A full independent blind re-run was not performed due to resource constraints. Minor discrepancies in inlet velocity profile specification were identified and corrected during partial review. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis model adopts the Giersiepen-Wurzinger (GW) power-law formulation, which is widely used but known to overpredict haemolysis in regions of recirculation and underpredict in high-shear thin-gap regions. The k-ω SST turbulence closure is applied; its applicability to rotating blood-contacting passages at transitional Reynolds numbers is not validated for this geometry class. No model-form uncertainty quantification (e.g., Bayesian model averaging across alternative haemolysis models) was performed. Required Gradation 5 demands rigorous model-form UQ; achieved Gradation 2 reflects use of a single unvalidated constitutive model without sensitivity analysis across model alternatives."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be characterised with probability distributions and propagated through the simulation via Monte Carlo or equivalent UQ method. Gradation 4 requires that input uncertainty contributions are ranked by Sobol sensitivity indices and that dominant inputs are validated against independent measurements.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed over six input parameters (viscosity, inlet flow rate, rotational speed, GW model coefficients α and β, and red blood cell volume fraction). Sobol first-order indices computed; rotational speed and GW coefficient β are dominant contributors. Independent validation of β against published erythrocyte fragility data was not performed. Achieved Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples must be characterised for haematocrit, mean corpuscular volume, and donor variability. Gradation 3 requires at least three independent blood or analog batches with documented lot-to-lot variability analysis.",
      "rationale": "Two batches of glycerol-water blood analog were prepared and tested. Lot-to-lot viscosity variability was measured at ±2.1%. A third batch was not prepared due to scheduling constraints. Haematocrit equivalence is inherent to the analog formulation; no donor variability applies. Achieved Gradation 2 due to insufficient number of independent sample batches."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in the validation model must be demonstrably equivalent to those of the COU model. Gradation 4 requires a formal parameter equivalency matrix with quantified deviations and sensitivity analysis for each parameter that differs between validation and COU configurations.",
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency matrix was constructed comparing the FDA generic pump validation configuration to the VAD COU configuration. Key deviations include impeller diameter (52 mm vs 48 mm), design flow rate (6 L/min vs 5 L/min), and inlet cannula geometry (straight vs angled). Sensitivity analyses for flow rate and diameter deviations were performed. Inlet cannula geometry sensitivity was not analysed. Achieved Gradation 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Following sponsor review, the credibility assessment for COU2 was accepted with documented gaps. The assessment team acknowledged that multiple credibility factors — including Discretization Error, Model Form, and Relevance of Validation Activities — do not meet their required levels at MRL 5. The decision to accept reflects a risk-informed determination that the Monte Carlo UQ bounds on hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold with 90% confidence, and that the identified gaps are being addressed in a follow-on simulation campaign. The discretization error factor in particular was accepted without a formally registered acceptanceCriteria record; the rationale narrative captures the intent but the structured criterion was not completed prior to the decision deadline.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
